cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC 

The paper presents a new decision procedure for the logic WS1S, which is a sub-logic of first-order logic. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with automata and language inclusion, which are topics covered in cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The pruning techniques used in the paper are related to subsumption and early termination, which are topics covered in cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
